    <h2>Liam Richardson - CV</h2>

    <p>I am an Interactive Developer with an extensive and in depth knowledge of Front End build and delivery. As a department lead, I have been responsible for the Front End output of a well respected agency. I have also lead a team of developers and freelancers, working with clients and other department leads. I am comfortable with all stages of the project life-cycle. Working closely with Design and Development Leads, I am able to plan the approach and process of a project. I often take part in the creative process, forming ideas and solutions to creative or technical problems. Thanks to this, as well as strong communication skills, I often act as the go-to point of contact for colleges and clients.
    </p>
    <p>I have worked with public organisations, SME’s and large brands to develop Interactive campaigns, responsive websites, and mobile specific sites and apps. Outside of the office, I volunteer with charities to help with their websites. I regularly attend web events and meet-ups, as well as working with friends to develop sites for their own projects. The following is a brief list of the technologies, software and tools I have experience in:</p>

