    <p>Further to this, I have worked on projects that have involved Node, Backbone, CoffeeScript, PhoneGap among others, though I still class myself as a beginner in these areas.</p>

    <h3>Employment:</h3>

    <h4>Lead Web Developer, Beef Ltd, Bristol - <span>May 2012 - April 2014</span></h4>
    <p>After progressing to the role of Lead Web Developer, I became responsible for Front End Development within the agency. As well as ensuring the quality of work undertaken, I lead the Web Development team in their day to day tasks. I support their ongoing development, insuring disciplines, best practice and standards met. I coordinate with the Development, Design and Account Leads, to devise new ideas, concepts and solutions that best meet a clients requirements. </p>

    <p>On small to medium scale websites, I am often the Technical Lead, working with off-the-shelf CMS's and applications. I am able to direct the technical direction or projects, as well as design features and advise on the feasibility of creative concepts. I often work with clients in meetings and conference calls, gathering requirements, scoping and prototyping technical solutions. Working with Producers and Account Managers I help define requirements, scope work and give time estimations. I also write technical documentation such as functional specifications, features and statements of work.</p>

    <h4>Front End Developer, Beef Ltd, Bristol - <span>June 2010 - May 2012</span></h4>
    After completing my degree I was offered a role with Beef based upon my performance during my placement year. During this period, I continued my technical development, learning new technologies, methodologies and best practice, moving quickly from a junior to mid level role. I worked with Design and Development teams to best realise the creative and technical goals of projects.

    <h4>Placement Year with Beef Ltd, Bristol - <span>August 2008 - July 2009</span></h4>
    I completed a placement year between the 2nd and 3rd years of my degree. I worked on a range of internal and client projects. My role mostly involved developing HTML, CSS and some JavaScript. As the year progressed I became more involved with the full project process, working more with Technical and Design teams.

